# UI Rules

## Design System

- Tailwind CSS 4 with CSS custom properties for the color palette.
- Dark theme only for V1. Colors are defined in `apps/desktop/src/index.css`.
- Shared components live in `packages/ui/`. Page-specific components live in `apps/desktop/src/`.

## Color Variables

```
--color-bg             #0f1117    Page background
--color-surface        #1a1d27    Sidebar, cards
--color-surface-raised #232736    Hover states, elevated cards
--color-border         #2e3347    Borders, dividers
--color-text-primary   #e8eaf0    Primary text
--color-text-secondary #8b90a5    Secondary text
--color-text-muted     #5c6178    Disabled/placeholder text
--color-accent         #6c8cff    Interactive elements
--color-success        #4ade80    Success states
--color-warning        #fbbf24    Warnings
--color-error          #f87171    Errors
```

## UX Standards

- The UI should feel calm, high-signal, private, and inspectable.
- Foreground user state (projects, themes, patterns) — not raw files.
- No gamification, no noisy cards, no unexplained intelligence claims.
- Every derived entity shown in the UI must be traceable to evidence.
- Zustand for local UI state (import progress, filters). Keep stores minimal.

## Component Patterns

- Components accept typed props — no `any` or loose object shapes.
- Shared components expose `className` for Tailwind composition where useful.
- Use `NavLink` from react-router-dom for navigation with active state styling.
